Gesture Recognition Flask API

This project integrates a pre-trained gesture recognition model into a Flask backend API. The API processes input gesture data and returns the recognized sign.
gesture_project/
├── app.py
├── models/
│   └── gesture_model.py
│   └── islr-fp16-192-8-seed42-fold0-best.h5
├── src/
│   └── backbone.py
│   └── landmarks_extraction.py
│   └── config.py
│   └── utils.py
│   └── sign_to_prediction_index_map.json
├── requirements.txt
├── README
├── venv/


Requirements

Ensure you have Python 3.6+ installed. Create a virtual environment and install dependencies using the provided requirements.txt.

Components:

gesture.py : contains the pre-trained model using TensorFlow
/predict : endpoint that accepts JSON input, configured to handle POST requests and process input data
request.json : used to retreive data,
np.frombuffer : processes the frame data 
    - added exception handling to manage possible errors during landmarks extraction

Testing

Use curl or Postman to send a POST request to your /predict endpoint:
Curl:
    curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/predict -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"frame": "your_encoded_frame_data_here"}'
Postman: 
    Set the request type to POST.
    Set the URL to http://127.0.0.1:5000/predict.
    Add a JSON body with a sample frame data.